    <td class="roweven" valign="top" nowrap>7.0</td>
    <td class="roweven" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=96">Charles Campbell</a></i></td>
    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">AsNeeded now uses Thomas's idea for producing a &quot;ANcmds.vim&quot; plugin with skeleton commands. Plus some bugfixes.&nbsp;&nbsp;With this feature, commands in scripts in the AsNeeded/ directory act as if they're always available, even when the scripts haven't been loaded.<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
        <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><a href="download_script.php?src_id=5429">AsNeeded.vim.gz</a></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><b>12</b></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><i>2006-03-14</i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap>6.0</td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=96">Charles Campbell</a></i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">(bugfix) AsNeeded needs to work around several options that the user may set.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, if a plugin changed one of these, AsNeeded &quot;restored&quot; the option at the time that AsNeeded was invoked, thereby overriding whatever the plugin/map etc may have set.&nbsp;&nbsp;AsNeeded now restores the options, then sources the plugin/map etc.</td>
</tr>
